children.name: fat a1
children.definition: fat having too much flesh on your body. it isrudeto tell sb that they are fat:béo
examples: ▪ peter was a fat little boy.
▪ after thirty years, teddy looked just the same, only a little fatter.
▪ most fat people simply eat too much by normal standards.
▪ though she weighed only six stone, she thought she was fat.
get fat
▪ i’m getting too fat for my clothes.

children.name: overweight b2
children.definition: overweighttoofat, especially so that you need to lose some weight in order to be more healthy or attractive:béo phì, thừa cân
examples: the doctor said i was slightly overweight and that i needed more exercise.
the majority of overweight people who diet tend to gain the weight back within a few years.
5 kilos/ 10 pounds etc overweight
my mother is about 50 pounds overweight.
grossly overweightextremely overweight
people who are grossly overweight are more likely to suffer from high blood pressure.

children.name: big a1
children.definition: big/large  fat - use this especially when youdo not want to say ‘fat’because it would be impolite:
examples: ▪ even though she’s big, rosemary is an attractive woman.
▪ it’s often difficult for large people to find fashionable clothes that fit them.
▪ mrs. medlock is a large woman, with a very red face and bright black eyes.
▪ he runs quite fast for a big man.

children.name: plump c2
children.definition: plump fat, especially in apleasantandattractiveway: bụ bẫm , đầy đặn
examples: ▪ stevie is a plump healthy-looking child.
▪ frieda’s mother was a plump, cheerful woman, quick with a laugh.
▪ he’s a little on the plump side, but nevertheless quite handsome

children.name: chubby x
children.definition: chubby (especially of a smallchild)fat in a pleasant, healthy-looking way: mũm mĩm mập mạp
examples: the baby was pink and chubby.
who’s that chubby little girl with the dark hair

children.name: portly x
children.definition: portly/ˈpɔːʳtli/  (especially of a fairly old man) fat and round - used especially in literature: béo tròn
examples: the bishop was a dignified, portly man, with thinning white hair.
the portly figure of general von hindenburg

children.name: hefty x
children.definition: hefty big and fat, but also tall and strong: vạm vỡ
examples: both of myra’s sons were hefty, energetic boys.
the mechanic was a big hefty man who could lift up the front of a truck with his bare hands.

children.name: beefy x
children.definition: beefy  strong but also a little fat and unattractive:béo khỏe
examples: the second prisoner was a fat-faced beefy fellow who smelled of sweat.
amanda and tina were both beefy, sporty types.

children.name: burly x
children.definition: burly a burly man is big, strong, and heavy, in a way that may make you feel nervous:lực lưỡng
examples: the farmer was a big, burly man with a red face.

children.name: fatty x
children.definition: fatty/ fatso/lardass    a rude word used for a fat person con mập, thằng mập:
examples: hey! fatso! pull up a couple of chairs!

children.name: a fat part of the body
fat a1
children.definition: fat béo
examples: ▪ sally hates going swimming -- she thinks her legs are too fat.
▪ the colonel rubbed his fat stomach, reaching for something from the table to put into his mouth.
▪ my stomach’s much fatter than yours.

children.name: stubby x
children.definition: stubby/stumpy body parts that arestubby or stumpyare short and thick: lùn mập
examples: pheasants have short stubby wings which enable them to fly very fast and low.
a fat little boy with stumpy legs

children.name: flabby x
children.definition: flabby  covered in soft loose fat in a way that looks unattractive: nhũn , nhão , mềm
examples: her body was getting old and flabby.
john’s flabby white thighs wobbled as he walked across the beach.

children.name: chubby x
children.definition: chubby (especially of children) fat and round in an attractive way: mũm mĩm mập mạp
examples: the baby reached out with its chubby little fingers.
mark’s cheeks were slightly chubby.

children.name: plump c2
children.definition: plump/plʌmp/  pleasantly fat: đầy đặn, phúng phính
examples: the doctor’s wife had a plump face and a small mouth.
paula had silver bracelets on her plump arms.

children.name: pudgy x
children.definition: podgy/ pudgy   small and fat, especially in an amusing way: béo múp
examples: his pudgy little fingers were covered in chocolate.
elsie had a large body and a podgy face.

children.name: full x
children.definition: full fat and round in an attractive way:béo, dầy, tròn
examples: joanna’s full red lips were fixed in an inviting smile.
a black necklace hung down over her full breasts.

children.name: put on weight b1
children.definition: put on weight to get fatter and heavier: lên cân
examples: john’s put on a lot of weight recently, hasn’t he?
put on 5 kilos/ 2 lbs etc
i put on several pounds while i was on holiday, so now i’m on a strict diet.

children.name: gain weight b1
children.definition: gain weight  to become fatter and heavier, especially until you reach the weight you should be: tăng cân
examples: when i was young, i could eat all i wanted without gaining weight.
gain 2 kilos/4 lbs etc tăng 2 kí, 4 pound
ben’s gained at least five kilos since he was born.

children.name: fill out x
children.definition: fill out to start getting fatter often after being too thin or because they have grown older:tăng cân
examples: gerry was terribly thin when he came out of hospital, but he’s filled out a lot since then.
sue looks much healthier now and her face has started to fill out.

children.name: fatten up x
children.definition: fatten sb up  to make sb fatter because they are too thin - often used: vỗ béo
examples: the women in his family were always trying to fatten him up.
you're just trying to fatten me up.

children.name: fatten up x
children.definition: fatten up to make an animal fatter so that it will produce more meat : vỗ béo
examples: fatten up sth/ fatten sth up
the farmers are fattening up their cattle and getting them ready for market.
these cattle are being fattened up for slaughter.

children.name: obese c1
children.definition: obeseextremelyfat in a way that is dangerous to your health: béo phì
examples: glenda is not just fat, she’s obese.
a special summer camp for obese children and teens
clinically obeseobese according to medical measurements béo phì lâm sàng
he may not be clinically obese, but he certainly needs to lose a lot of weight.
obesity[c1] [u noun] the condition of being too fat in a way that is dangerous to your health - used especially in medical contexts: bệnh béo phì
obesity can lead to heart disorders and other health problems.
the program is aimed at reducing obesity among women.
childhoodobesity
a diet that is high in fat can lead to obesity.

children.name: a person who is fat and not very tall
dumpy x
children.definition: dumpy (especially a woman or child) short and fat: béo lùn
examples: clara was a plain, dumpy woman, several years older than her husband.
in his youth, william had been a dumpy little boy who ate too many sweets.
i think this skirt makes me look dumpy.

children.name: tubby x
children.definition: tubby  sb who is tubby is short and has a fat, round stomach:to béo
examples: the banker was a tubby, jolly-looking man.
he’s getting a bit tubby -- too much of his wife’s cooking i expect.

children.name: stout x
children.definition: stout (especially a middle-aged person) quite fat and solid-looking, especially around the waist:tròn mập
examples: a stout woman in a tweed coat was standing outside the door.
amy was now stout and matronly, the mother of three children.

children.name: paunch x
children.definition: paunch a man who has a paunch has a large stomach:bụng bự
examples: you’re getting a paunch, did you know that?
merv lay back in his chair with his hands crossed above his paunch, listening to the radio.
wally crossed the mirrored lobby, sucking in his paunch as he caught sight of himself.

children.name: pot belly x
children.definition: pot belly a round stomach that sticks out at the front, especially when this is the result of eating or drinking too much: bụng phệ
examples: larry was just a regular guy: short, with a pot belly and moustache.
you really should do something about that pot belly of yours.
pot-bellied[adj]bụng phệ
our history teacher was a balding, pot-bellied man of about 50.
pot-bellied politicians, puffing cigars

children.name: beer gut x
children.definition: beer gut informal a fat stomach caused by drinking too much beer: bụng bia
examples: his beer gut was popping the buttons on his shirt.
at only seventeen, lonny already had the beginnings of a beer gut.

children.name: spare tyre x
children.definition: spare tyre/ spare tire  a ring of fat around the waist:nếp bụng mỡ
examples: you should go on a diet -- look at that spare tyre.

children.name: middle-age spread x
children.definition: middle-age spread  the fat around the waist that people gradually get as they grow older: ngấn bụng
examples: a lot of people start to get middle-age spread once they pass 30.
